22/10/2009
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Police arrested six people Wednesday (October 21st) on suspicion of illegal stock dealings at Croatian food producer Podravka.
Among those detained are the former and current executives of the company -- Darko Marinac and Zdravko Sestak.
They and the others were allegedly involved in a series of financial transactions that began in 2006, intending to purchase Podravka's shares and take over the firm using its own money.
Investigators say they cost the state 34.5m euros in losses.
(HRT, HINA, Nova TV, Vecernji List, Reuters, AP - 21/10/09)
